{"title_page": "Outfit7", "text_new": "{{short description|Creator of the Talking Tom and Friends media franchise}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = Outfit7 Limited\n| logo                = Outfit7 Logo 2018.svg\n| type                = [[Subsidiary]]\n| industry            = [[Video game industry|Video games]], [[Web series|Web series distribution]]\n| founded             = {{start date and age|df=yes|2009|7}} in [[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]]\n| founder             = {{Plainlist|\n* Samo Login\n* Iza Login\n}}\n| hq_location_city    = [[Pissouri]]\n| hq_location_country = [[Cyprus]]\n| area_served         = Worldwide\n| key_people          = {{Plainlist|\n* Samo Login <small>Co-founder</small>\n* Iza Login <small>Co-founder</small>\n* Jure Prek <small>Advisor</small>\n* \u017diga Vavpoti\u010d <small>[[Chairman of the Board]]</small>\n* Xinyu Qian <small>[[Chief executive officer|CEO]]</small>\n}}\n| parent              = Zhejiang Jinke Entertainment Culture Co., Ltd. (2017\u2013present)\n| num_employees       = 250<ref name=\"corporate\">{{cite web |url=https://outfit7.com/about-us/ |title=About Us |website=Outfit7 |accessdate=27 April 2020}}</ref>\n| num_employees_year  = 2020\n| revenue             = $130 million <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.owler.com/company/outfit7|title=Owler - Outfit7|last=|first=|date=April 27, 2020|website=Owler|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 27, 2020}}</ref>\n| website             = {{URL|http://www.outfit7.com/|outfit7.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Outfit7 Limited''' is a [[Slovenia]]n [[video game developer]], best known as the creator of the ''[[Talking Tom and Friends]]'' app and media franchise. The company was founded by Samo and Iza Login. The company operates in 7 studios worldwide and almost exclusively focuses on [[Mobile game|mobile games]] related to the ''Talking Tom and Friends'' franchise. In January 2017, the company was acquired by United Luck Consortium and then sold to Zhejiang Jinke for over USD 1 billion.\n\n==History==\n\n=== Founding and early years ===\nOutfit7 was founded by Samo and Iza Login, who had studied computer science in college and wanted to get into the mobile app business following the debut of the [[App Store (iOS)|Apple App Store]]. In 2009, they invested  $250,000 (\u20ac180,000)  with six friends and set up on office in [[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]], where they developed some apps. Their first few attempts \u2014 a soccer app, a travel guide to [[Iceland]] and a \"wealth affirmation app\" were unsuccessful. After six months of attempts, they developed a children's app called ''Talking Tom Cat'', in which an animated cat named Tom would repeat in a \"high-pitched helium squeak whatever is spoken into an iPhone\u2019s microphone\" along with other reactions to feeding and petting.<ref name=\"bloomberg history\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2017-05-17/why-did-a-chinese-peroxide-company-pay-1-billion-for-a-talking-cat |title=Why Did a Chinese Peroxide Company Pay $1 Billion for a Talking Cat? |author= |date=17 May 2017 |publisher= |accessdate=25 May 2017 |via=www.bloomberg.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Talking Tom and Friends ===\n{{Main|Talking Tom and Friends}}\nThe ''Talking Tom and Friends'' franchise was created with the launch of the ''Talking Tom Cat'' app. It focused on anthropomorphic cats and dogs repeating things said to it by the user, before shifting focus to other apps such as endless-runner games, virtual pet games and the like.\n\nThe franchise reached 300 million downloads 19 months after its launch. The app franchise then went on to hit one billion downloads in June 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tech/news/a490312/talking-friends-apps-reach-1-billion-downloads.html |title=Talking Friends apps reach 1 billion downloads |work=[[Digital Spy]] |date=14 June 2013 |accessdate=30 July 2014 |author=Langshaw, Mark}}</ref> Talking Tom and Friends apps have been downloaded over 12 billion times as of April 2020.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/talking-tom-coolest-cat-back-090000277.html |title=Talking Tom \u2013 the Coolest Cat is Back \u2013 Bigger, Better and Cuter Than Before |work=[[Business Wire]] |date=14 June 2013 |accessdate=30 July 2014 |author=N/A}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://outfit7.com/|title=Outfit7|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n\n== Products ==\n\n=== Talking Tom and Friends ===\n\n==== Apps ====\n\n* Talking Tom\n* Talking Gina\n* Talking Ben\n* Talking Tom 2\n* Talking News\n* Talking Pierre\n* Tom\u2019s Love Letters\n* Tom Loves Angela\n* Talking Ginger\n* Talking Angela\n* Talking Ginger 2\n* My Talking Tom\n* My Talking Angela\n* Talking Tom Jetski\n* Talking Tom Bubble Shooter\n* Talking Tom Gold Run\n* My Talking Hank\n* Talking Angela Color Splash\n* Talking Tom Camp\n* Talking Tom Pool\n* Talking Tom Jetski 2\n* Talking Tom Candy Run\n* Talking Tom Cake Jump\n* Talking Tom Jump Up\n* My Talking Tom 2\n* Talking Tom Fun Fair\n* Talking Tom Hero Dash\n* Talking Tom Splash Force\n\n==== Web Series ====\n\n* Talking Friends (2012)\n* [[Talking Tom and Friends (TV series)|Talking Tom and Friends]] (2014-present)\n* Talking Tom Shorts (2014-present)\n* Talking Tom and Friends Minis (2016-2018)\n* Talking Tom Heroes (2019-present)\n\n=== Other apps ===\n\n* Tiki Tag<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.outfit7.tikitag&hl=en_IN|title=Tiki Tag \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n* Disco Ant<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.outfit7.discoant&hl=en_IN|title=Disco Ant \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n* Jigty Jelly<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.outfit7.jigty.jelly&hl=en_IN|title=Jigty Jelly \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n* Jigty Jigsaw Puzzles<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.outfit7.jigtyfree&hl=en_IN|title=Jigty Jigsaw Puzzles \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n* Swamp Attack<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.outfit7.movingeye.swampattack&hl=en_IN|title=Swamp Attack \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n\n== Corporate affairs ==\n\n=== Studios ===\nOutfit7 operates offices in 7 cities in [[Europe]] and [[Asia]]. The company currently operates in [[London]], Ljubljana, [[Barcelona]], [[Mumbai]], Pissouri, [[Hong Kong]] and [[Beijing]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://outfit7.com/about-us/|title=Outfit7 - About Us|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n\n=== Acquisition and Leadership change ===\nIn 2016, Samo and Iza Login hired [[Goldman Sachs]] to arrange for a deal to sell their company.<ref name=\"bloomberg history\" /> In 20 January 2017 it was announced in a press release that Outfit7 was sold to United Luck Holdings Consortium, a [[China]]-based group for US$1 billion.<ref name=\"venturebeat\" /> However, four days later, another press release indicated that United Luck would sell Outfit7 to a Chinese chemical company, Zhejiang Jinke Peroxide Company, which was renamed to Zhejiang Jinke Entertainment Culture Co. Ltd after it had purchased a Chinese game developer.<ref name=\"bloomberg history\" /><ref name=\"bloomberg2\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-01-25/china-s-jinke-to-buy-gamemaker-outfit7-for-at-least-1-billion |title=China\u2019s Jinke Slumps on Plan to Buy Talking Tom Maker Outfit7 |author= |date=25 January 2017 |publisher= |accessdate=25 May 2017 |via=www.bloomberg.com}}</ref> There was some confusion over who owned Outfit7 given that Jinke had disclosed plans to buy a 10% stake of United Luck. In March 2017, the agreement to sell Outfit7 to Jinke was signed.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://en.yibada.com/articles/197138/20170306/jinke-signs-agreement-for-plans-on-buying-famous-talking-tom-app-maker-competes-with-united-luck-group.htm |title=Jinke Signs Agreement to Buy Famous Talking Tom App Maker, Competes with United Luck Group |first=Jomel |last=Javier |date=6 March 2017 |website=yibada.com |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"forbes sold\">{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/janeho/2017/03/02/talking-tom-app-maker-outfit7-flipped-to-chinas-jinke-at-over-1-billion/ |title=Talking Tom App Maker Outfit7 Flipped To China's Jinke At Over $1 Billion |first=Jane |last=Ho |date= |website=forbes.com |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref> Samo Login remained on board as company director, and Iza Login remained as an advisor.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://2tm.si/chinese-company-jinke-becomes-the-third-owner-of-outfit-7/?lang=en |title=- News 2TM |author= |date=13 March 2017 |website=2tm.si |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"venturebeat\">{{cite web |url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/01/20/talking-tom-maker-outfit7-confirms-it-has-been-sold-to-united-luck-consortium-for-1-billion/ |title=Talking Tom maker Outfit7 confirms it has been sold to United Luck Consortium for $1 billion |author= |date=20 January 2017 |website=venturebeat.com |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://opencorporates.com/companies/gb/08725441 |title=OUTFIT7 LIMITED :: OpenCorporates |author= |date= |website=opencorporates.com |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref> In July 2018, Xinyu Qian became the CEO, while Prek took up the post of advisor.<ref name=\"NewCEO\">{{Cite web|url=https://outfit7.com/2018/07/outfit7-names-xinyu-qian-as-new-ceo/|title=Outfit7 names Xinyu Qian as new CEO|date=July 1, 2018|website=Outfit7|access-date=July 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website|https://outfit7.com/}}\n\n[[Category:Software companies based in London]]\n[[Category:Video game development companies]]\n[[Category:Video game companies established in 2009]]\n[[Category:International Game Developers Association members]]\n[[Category:Talking Tom and Friends]]\n[[Category:Video game companies of Slovenia]]\n[[Category:Video game companies of the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Creator of the Talking Tom and Friends media franchise}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = Outfit7 Limited\n| logo                = Outfit7 Logo 2018.svg\n| type                = [[Subsidiary]]\n| industry            = [[Video game industry|Video games]], [[Web series|Web series distribution]]\n| founded             = {{start date and age|df=yes|2009|7}} in [[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]]\n| founder             = {{Plainlist|\n* Samo Login\n* Iza Login\n}}\n| hq_location_city    = [[Pissouri]]\n| hq_location_country = [[Cyprus]]\n| area_served         = Worldwide\n| key_people          = {{Plainlist|\n* Samo Login <small>Co-founder</small>\n* Iza Login <small>Co-founder</small>\n* Jure Prek <small>Advisor</small>\n* \u017diga Vavpoti\u010d <small>[[Chairman of the Board]]</small>\n* Xinyu Qian <small>[[Chief executive officer|CEO]]</small>\n}}\n| parent              = Zhejiang Jinke Entertainment Culture Co., Ltd. (2017\u2013present)\n| num_employees       = 250<ref name=\"corporate\">{{cite web |url=https://outfit7.com/about-us/ |title=About Us |website=Outfit7 |accessdate=27 April 2020}}</ref>\n| num_employees_year  = 2020\n| revenue             = $130 million <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.owler.com/company/outfit7|title=Owler - Outfit7|last=|first=|date=April 27, 2020|website=Owler|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 27, 2020}}</ref>\n| website             = {{URL|http://www.outfit7.com/|outfit7.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Outfit7 Limited''' is a [[Slovenia]]n [[video game developer]], best known as the creator of the ''[[Talking Tom and Friends]]'' app and media franchise. The company was founded by Samo and Iza Login. The company operates in 7 studios worldwide and almost exclusively focuses on [[Mobile game|mobile games]] related to the ''Talking Tom and Friends'' franchise. In January 2017, the company was acquired by United Luck Consortium and then sold to Zhejiang Jinke for over USD 1 billion.\n\n==History==\n\n=== Founding and early years ===\nOutfit7 was founded by Samo and Iza Login, who had studied computer science in college and wanted to get into the mobile app business following the debut of the [[App Store (iOS)|Apple App Store]]. In 2009, they invested  $250,000 (\u20ac180,000)  with six friends and set up on office in [[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]], where they developed some apps. Their first few attempts \u2014 a soccer app, a travel guide to [[Iceland]] and a \"wealth affirmation app\" were unsuccessful. After six months of attempts, they developed a children's app called ''Talking Tom Cat'', in which an animated cat named Tom would repeat in a \"high-pitched helium squeak whatever is spoken into an iPhone\u2019s microphone\" along with other reactions to feeding and petting.<ref name=\"bloomberg history\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2017-05-17/why-did-a-chinese-peroxide-company-pay-1-billion-for-a-talking-cat |title=Why Did a Chinese Peroxide Company Pay $1 Billion for a Talking Cat? |author= |date=17 May 2017 |publisher= |accessdate=25 May 2017 |via=www.bloomberg.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Talking Tom and Friends ===\n{{Main|Talking Tom and Friends}}\nThe ''Talking Tom and Friends'' franchise was created with the launch of the ''Talking Tom Cat'' app. It focused on anthropomorphic cats and dogs repeating things said to it by the user, before shifting focus to other apps such as endless-runner games, virtual pet games and the like.\n\nThe franchise reached 300 million downloads 19 months after its launch. The app franchise then went on to hit one billion downloads in June 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tech/news/a490312/talking-friends-apps-reach-1-billion-downloads.html |title=Talking Friends apps reach 1 billion downloads |work=[[Digital Spy]] |date=14 June 2013 |accessdate=30 July 2014 |author=Langshaw, Mark}}</ref> Talking Tom and Friends apps have been downloaded over 12 billion times as of April 2020.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/talking-tom-coolest-cat-back-090000277.html |title=Talking Tom \u2013 the Coolest Cat is Back \u2013 Bigger, Better and Cuter Than Before |work=[[Business Wire]] |date=14 June 2013 |accessdate=30 July 2014 |author=N/A}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://outfit7.com/|title=Outfit7|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n\n== Products ==\n\n=== Talking Tom and Friends ===\n\n==== Apps ====\n\n* Talking Tom\n* Talking Gina\n* Talking Ben\n* Talking Tom 2\n* Talking News\n* Talking Pierre\n* Tom\u2019s Love Letters\n* Tom Loves Angela\n* Talking Ginger\n* Talking Angela\n* Talking Ginger 2\n* My Talking Tom\n* My Talking Angela\n* Talking Tom Jetski\n* Talking Tom Bubble Shooter\n* Talking Tom Gold Run\n* My Talking Hank\n* Talking Angela Color Splash\n* Talking Tom Camp\n* Talking Tom Pool\n* Talking Tom Jetski 2\n* Talking Tom Candy Run\n* Talking Tom Cake Jump\n* Talking Tom Jump Up\n* My Talking Tom 2\n* Talking Tom Fun Fair\n* Talking Tom Hero Dash\n* Talking Tom Splash Force\n\n==== Web Series ====\n\n* Talking Friends (2012)\n* [[Talking Tom and Friends (TV series)|Talking Tom and Friends]] (2014-present)\n* Talking Tom Shorts (2014-present)\n* Talking Tom and Friends Minis (2016-2018)\n* Talking Tom Heroes (2019-present)\n\n=== Other apps ===\n\n* Tiki Tag<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.outfit7.tikitag&hl=en_IN|title=Tiki Tag \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n* Disco Ant<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.outfit7.discoant&hl=en_IN|title=Disco Ant \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n* Jigty Jelly<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.outfit7.jigty.jelly&hl=en_IN|title=Jigty Jelly \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n* Jigty Jigsaw Puzzles<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.outfit7.jigtyfree&hl=en_IN|title=Jigty Jigsaw Puzzles \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n* Swamp Attack<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.outfit7.movingeye.swampattack&hl=en_IN|title=Swamp Attack \u2013 Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n\n== Corporate affairs ==\n\n=== Studios ===\nOutfit7 operates offices in 7 cities in [[Europe]] and [[Asia]]. The company currently operates in [[London]], Ljubljana, [[Barcelona]], [[Mumbai]], Pissouri, [[Hong Kong]] and [[Beijing]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://outfit7.com/about-us/|title=Outfit7 - About Us|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n\n=== Acquisition and Leadership change ===\nIn 2016, Samo and Iza Login hired [[Goldman Sachs]] to arrange for a deal to sell their company.<ref name=\"bloomberg history\" /> In 20 January 2017 it was announced in a press release that Outfit7 was sold to United Luck Holdings Consortium, a [[China]]-based group for US$1 billion.<ref name=\"venturebeat\" /> However, four days later, another press release indicated that United Luck would sell Outfit7 to a Chinese chemical company, Zhejiang Jinke Peroxide Company, which was renamed to Zhejiang Jinke Entertainment Culture Co. Ltd after it had purchased a Chinese game developer.<ref name=\"bloomberg history\" /><ref name=\"bloomberg2\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-01-25/china-s-jinke-to-buy-gamemaker-outfit7-for-at-least-1-billion |title=China\u2019s Jinke Slumps on Plan to Buy Talking Tom Maker Outfit7 |author= |date=25 January 2017 |publisher= |accessdate=25 May 2017 |via=www.bloomberg.com}}</ref> There was some confusion over who owned Outfit7 given that Jinke had disclosed plans to buy a 10% stake of United Luck. In March 2017, the agreement to sell Outfit7 to Jinke was signed.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://en.yibada.com/articles/197138/20170306/jinke-signs-agreement-for-plans-on-buying-famous-talking-tom-app-maker-competes-with-united-luck-group.htm |title=Jinke Signs Agreement to Buy Famous Talking Tom App Maker, Competes with United Luck Group |first=Jomel |last=Javier |date=6 March 2017 |website=yibada.com |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"forbes sold\">{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/janeho/2017/03/02/talking-tom-app-maker-outfit7-flipped-to-chinas-jinke-at-over-1-billion/ |title=Talking Tom App Maker Outfit7 Flipped To China's Jinke At Over $1 Billion |first=Jane |last=Ho |date= |website=forbes.com |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref> Samo Login remained on board as company director, and Iza Login indicated on her LinkedIn that she was an advisor.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://2tm.si/chinese-company-jinke-becomes-the-third-owner-of-outfit-7/?lang=en |title=- News 2TM |author= |date=13 March 2017 |website=2tm.si |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"venturebeat\">{{cite web |url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/01/20/talking-tom-maker-outfit7-confirms-it-has-been-sold-to-united-luck-consortium-for-1-billion/ |title=Talking Tom maker Outfit7 confirms it has been sold to United Luck Consortium for $1 billion |author= |date=20 January 2017 |website=venturebeat.com |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://opencorporates.com/companies/gb/08725441 |title=OUTFIT7 LIMITED :: OpenCorporates |author= |date= |website=opencorporates.com |accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref> In July 2018, Xinyu Qian became the CEO, while Prek took up the post of advisor.<ref name=\"NewCEO\">{{Cite web|url=https://outfit7.com/2018/07/outfit7-names-xinyu-qian-as-new-ceo/|title=Outfit7 names Xinyu Qian as new CEO|date=July 1, 2018|website=Outfit7|access-date=July 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website|https://outfit7.com/}}\n\n[[Category:Software companies based in London]]\n[[Category:Video game development companies]]\n[[Category:Video game companies established in 2009]]\n[[Category:International Game Developers Association members]]\n[[Category:Talking Tom and Friends]]\n[[Category:Video game companies of Slovenia]]\n[[Category:Video game companies of the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "RedBulbBlueBlood9911", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reworded certain phrases", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Outfit7"}
